captions.text: - Well hello everyone!
My name is Tyler Oakley,
and if you couldn’t tell,
I am here in Brighton at Zoe’s house,
and I was like, “You know what?
“Just because I am abroad
“and on vacation, and working,

“and filming a whole
bunch of videos for y’all
“doesn’t mean that I can’ sit down
“and do a little Q and Slay for you.”
So y’all sit back, relax, chillitate,
and just take a little moment,
because it is time for another Q and Slay.
Slaying Since 1999, which is literally
10 years younger than me, says,
”When was the last time you took a shit?”

I actually have proof of
the last time I took a shit.
Let me go get it, hold on.
So Zoe actually has a book that is called,
‘The Bathroom Guest Book’
and it has signed every single person
who’s ever shit here, so Sawyer, Tanya,
Jim Chapman, Joe Sugg (laughing).
Joe Sugg, Joe Sugg, Joe Sugg, Joe Sugg.
Joe Sugg poops a lot in this house.
Joey Graceffa, Troye Sivan,
Korey Kuhl, Connor Franta, Marcus Butler,
literally everyone.
And then the most recent entry is me.

And it even has a little
section where you can
give her a little score for everything,
like the ambiance, the cleanliness,
the comfort, the toilet tissue,
the amenities, the lighting, the privacy,
all of that, and then an overall grade.
I gave her an ‘A’ in everything
except privacy, because in Zoe’s house
there are no locks on the bathrooms,
which is disturbing because
one time out of the blue she just
flew open through the door and started

filming me while I was
naked in the shower.
And I was literally in there screaming.
Um, and then when I got out of the shower
she was just laying on her bed watching it
over and over, my naked body on her phone,
and I made her delete it.
So, thank you Zoe.
What was I talking about?
Oh, shitting at Zoe’s house.
It’s great!
auren says, “What is your favorite
”song of the moment?”
Currently I am really into Sia’s album.
Literally hit, after hit, after hit,
and you can tell because she writes
for so many people, but she clearly saved
her best songs for herself.

My number one favorite
is ‘Dressed in Black.’
I just think the lyrics are incredible.
I love the album, check it out.
The link, again, is in my Spotify.
Anistyn would like to know,

”What do you recommend on
Nature Box this month?”

As you guys know, I
recommend a new little snack
on Nature Box every single month.
This month, in July, I am recommending
the blueberry almonds!

They’re like little almonds,
normal little almonds,

but, like, coated with
blueberry flavoring.

They are so delicious
that on my flight here

I literally ate them
all, but I should have

kept some because I had
cute boys on my flight
literally everywhere all around me, and I
could’ve used them as, like, temptation
to come near me but I ate them all instead
because they were so good.
So if you use naturebox.com/tyler
you can get your first box for 50% off
if you sign up with that link.
It’s kind of the best thing ever,
because all you do is go to the website,
pick whatever stuff you want,

whatever snacks, whatever
size box you want,
and then they deliver those to your house

every single month and
you don’t have to go
interact with people at a grocery store.
It just comes right to your front door,
and then you get to eat everything
and it’s super healthy, and delicious,

and, like, low in trans-fats
and all those good things.
And obviously good temptation for boys

if you’re trying to lure
them to you on a plane.
So again, you’re welcome for the hook up.
Use naturebox.com/tyler for 50% off
your first box.
You’re welcome in advance.
@troyeandtyler says “What are your goals
”and aspirations for the near future?”
Um, you know, I have a lot of things
I need to get done.
So in the near, near, near future
I would say get through today.
I think that’s a pretty good rule of thumb

for anybody’s near future
goals and aspirations.

Just get through today,
because even though
today might be shitty,

or overwhelming, or a
little bit stressful,
you know what?

You have the same hours
in your day as Beyonce,
and somehow she gets through it!
So I think you can too.

Maddi says, “Will you
come to New Zealand?”
Obviously I would come to New Zealand.
I would love to come to New Zealand.
Someday I will, and Maddi, I am expecting
a hug when I arrive.
@itsjustalexiss says
“When did you start liking guys?”
Honestly, I was probably still in the womb
and I heard a guy through my mom’s, like,
outer layer of her, like, belly
and I was like “Oh, Daddy!”
Probably not my actual daddy,
because that would be weird.

But like I would be
calling other guys Daddy
and then be like “Yes, Daddy!”
Like I’d hear a nice manly voice and
I’m like “Mm!”
Like thirsty from the womb.
Not even able to quench my thirst
through an umbilical cord.
Since day one.
Andrea says “What weird things
”do I do when I’m home alone?”
Well I am currently at Zoe’s home alone,

so if I expose myself I
don’t want her to know
what I’m actually doing in her apartment
when I’m not filming, because girl,
I get up to some stuff.
(laughs)
It’s not like I, like, put her guinea pigs
up my ass or anything.
Or like, shit all over the floors,
or like, dry hump her table.
I swear I don’t do any of those things!

Emma says “How many
pillows do you sleep with?”
I usually sleep
with like a million pillows all around me.
I sleep in, like, a pillow cavern
of, like, epic proportions.

But while I’m here, I
have the cutest pillow.
Can I show you my pillow that
Zoe’s letting me sleep on?
How perfect is this?
It’s like everything that I’m looking for
in my entire life.

Natasha says, “What was
the last selfie you took?”
This is actually a funny story.

We were out to breakfast
with me, Alfie, and Zoe.
And anytime I’m hanging out with Alfie
he does this thing where he’ll act like

he’s about to show you
something on his phone,

and he’ll be like “Hey
look, check this out.”
And then as he’s showing it to you
he’ll actually take a picture.

And he will have caught
a bad picture of you
and he does this to me all the time!
So I try to do it to him.
But because I had it looking this way
as I was pointing it that way,

when I was supposed to
be pointing it that way
to take a picture of him,
but instead it took a picture of me,
and I still looked like a derp.

So this is the last selfie
that is on my phone.
Again, I fail at literally everything.
Jovanni says, “How often do you just stop
”and think, ‘I am so happy to be alive?’ “
And I would say probably not enough.
Um, I am really lucky.
I’m really blessed and priveleged

and I have so many amazing
things going for me.
Even though not everything is perfect
I do have a lot of really great things,
like you guys in my life,
and I really, I think I need to be

a little bit more conscious
of that day to day.
Because sometimes I forget how lucky I am
to have all of the things that I have.

Whether it’s, like, my
health, or my family
who is really supportive, or my friends
who are incredible and talented
and inspiring, or you guys who are
so encouraging and appreciative,

and just kind, and
generous and respectful.
And I am just really lucky, so
I am taking this moment, right now,

to say thank you to
anybody that’s watching
that is a part of that happiness that is
manifested in my life,
for multitudes of reasons.
Thank you.
I guess you think about being grateful

when you’re making, like,
an acceptance speech,
or when you have a huge accomplishment,
but it’s the day to day things

that I think you should
be even more grateful for
because that’s the life you live.

And if I didn’t have that
solid, solid foundation,

I don’t know if I would
be able to do and achieve

half of the things that
are actually happening
in my life.

So thank you for being
that rock solid foundation

that I have in my life,
whether you are my friends,
or my family, or my viewers,

or anybody that is a
positive little moment
in my life: thank you.
I’m sorry that was, like, mushy.
I’m just, I will stop right now.
”Get me motivated to study.”
Study!
Or else I’m gonna be really mad!
(laughing)
You should study because learning is,

like, a good thing, and
the more you can learn,
like, the better it is for you.
Megan says, “Give me a pet name.”
You little booger fart nugget butt!
Yes, you like it when I talk dirty to you?
(giggles)
So that is all I have for you guys today.
If you like today’s little Q & A,
be sure to give it a thumbs up.
I think we can get 100,000 thumbs up!
(snorts)
I have no rhyme or reason
for why you should give this a thumbs up,

but if you liked it let me
know by clicking the button.
That’s all I’m asking for.
It’s very simple.
If you would like to see my last Q & A,
click right there.
If you want to see my last Friday video
with Tanya and Jim, click right there.

If you would like to be
my Person of the Week
all you gotta do is go to
districtlines.com/tyleroakley
and get something real cute
and send me a self with you
being all adorable and stuff

on Twitter, and you might
be featured right there.
And don’t forget to subscribe.
We are almost at 5 million subscribers!
If you haven’t subscribed already,
I don’t know what you’re doing.
And if you haven’t
convinced your best friend to subscribe,
I mean who do you live with in your life?
(laughs)
I can’t even talk. I’m gonna go.
I’m gonna go hang out with Zoe,
and Alfie, and Marcus, and Nimbob,
and everyone here in the UK
that I am absolutely adoring.
So until next time,
later and good luck with your life,
and bye!
Oh!
